1
00:01:48,686 --> 00:01:50,953
[CENTRAL SOLDIER 1]
Fuhrer Bradley has returned?

2
00:01:52,453 --> 00:01:53,586
[CENTRAL SOLDIER 2]
With a vengeance!

3
00:01:53,620 --> 00:01:55,520
He destroyed a Briggs tank!

4
00:01:55,553 --> 00:01:58,386
Chew on that,
you lousy Briggs traitors!

5
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:00,020
Let's rally the
remaining troops...

6
00:02:00,053 --> 00:02:02,320
We're gonna retake
Central Command!

7
00:02:02,353 --> 00:02:04,020
[SOLDIERS GRUNT]

8
00:02:04,053 --> 00:02:06,386
[LAN FAN THINKING]
The Fuhrer is at the main gate?!

9
00:02:09,986 --> 00:02:11,686
Well...

10
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:14,853
This is the first time
I've actually laid eyes on him.

11
00:02:18,053 --> 00:02:20,886
So now I know what
the bastard who took

12
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:23,386
my granddaughter's
arm looks like!

13
00:02:29,053 --> 00:02:30,586
[IZUMI]
Is that so...?

14
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:32,886
You sacrifice our country...

15
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:35,753
just so you officials
can gain immortality...

16
00:02:35,786 --> 00:02:38,520
And enslave
the world as your own?

17
00:02:38,553 --> 00:02:40,353
[EDISON WHIMPERS]

18
00:02:40,386 --> 00:02:42,253
And I take it
that Fuhrer Bradley

19
00:02:42,286 --> 00:02:43,886
is also aware
of these plans?

20
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:47,020
[EDISON]
He was created to lead
this country for that purpose.

21
00:02:47,053 --> 00:02:49,353
[SOLDIERS WHISPER]

22
00:02:49,386 --> 00:02:50,520
Why shouldn't we do it?

23
00:02:50,553 --> 00:02:52,620
We're creating
a world without war!

24
00:02:52,653 --> 00:02:55,786
[IZUMI]
And you'd just have to
murder the world first.

25
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,586
It wouldn't die,
it would be reborn.

26
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:05,653
What you alchemists
refer to as reconstruction.

27
00:03:05,686 --> 00:03:08,953
We wouldn't be murdering
the population like you said...

28
00:03:08,986 --> 00:03:12,620
They would be given eternal life
while dwelling inside us!

29
00:03:12,653 --> 00:03:15,620
Don't you see we would bring
the world together as one?!

30
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:18,420
All as one...! And one as all!

31
00:03:18,453 --> 00:03:20,553
As the few chosen
ones of Amestris,

32
00:03:20,586 --> 00:03:22,786
we will bring unity
to the entire country!

33
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:23,520
[EDISON YELLS]

34
00:03:23,553 --> 00:03:26,253
[EDISON WHIMPERS]

35
00:03:26,286 --> 00:03:29,920
So there you have it.
You still on their side?

36
00:03:29,953 --> 00:03:33,253
The only thing these
guys care about is themselves.

37
00:03:33,286 --> 00:03:34,386
Will you help them?

38
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:37,286
Now wait... Listen, men...
You need to follow orders.

39
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:39,886
That's the only way I can
put in a good word for you.

40
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,953
[IZUMI YELLS]

41
00:03:42,753 --> 00:03:44,453
[THUD]

42
00:03:46,786 --> 00:03:48,820
I've spent my entire
life as a soldier

43
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:52,520
and it just feels wrong
to disobey my superiors.

44
00:03:52,553 --> 00:03:53,986
But I don't even
know what to believe

45
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:56,686
after hearing
all of this.

46
00:03:56,720 --> 00:04:00,486
You can't make up your own
mind after hearing their plans?

47
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:03,486
How can you follow a superior
you have no faith in?

48
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,020
That is not loyalty.

49
00:04:05,053 --> 00:04:07,686
That's mindless self-deception.

50
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:10,453
[SOLDIERS STAMMER]

51
00:04:10,486 --> 00:04:13,486
Believe in yourselves.

52
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,386
And choose life over death...

53
00:04:15,420 --> 00:04:18,653
Otherwise you've led
a shameful existence.

54
00:04:21,353 --> 00:04:23,586
[EDISON WHIMPERS]

55
00:04:30,653 --> 00:04:32,986
[ERIC] I have a family
right here in Central.

56
00:04:33,020 --> 00:04:34,553
[CASPER] So do I.

57
00:04:34,586 --> 00:04:36,920
[GUSTAV]
Yeah... We all do.

58
00:04:54,786 --> 00:04:56,720
[CASPER]
Well, sir...

59
00:04:56,753 --> 00:04:59,286
Consider this
our retirement.

60
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:07,320
Come in, Operations...
What's the status?

61
00:05:07,353 --> 00:05:09,286
[CARLY]
It's not exactly
favorable, sir.

62
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,820
The Central soldiers are
getting their second wind.

63
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:13,620
What's your current location?

64
00:05:13,653 --> 00:05:15,520
[OLIVIER]
We're in the Fuhrer's office.

65
00:05:15,553 --> 00:05:17,486
Any survivors?

66
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:18,820
We've been unable to contact

67
00:05:18,853 --> 00:05:21,486
any of our allies near
the office, General.

68
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:22,920
I've got a bad
feeling they've been

69
00:05:22,953 --> 00:05:25,453
surrounded by Central troops.

70
00:05:25,486 --> 00:05:26,420
[OLIVIER] Understood...

71
00:05:26,453 --> 00:05:29,920
Get out of there if
it gets too dangerous.

72
00:05:29,953 --> 00:05:31,886
Get out and leave me behind.

73
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,620
[CARLY EXHALES HEAVILY]

74
00:05:33,653 --> 00:05:36,486
Yes, sir.

75
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:40,386
[OLIVIER]
Well, this place is crawling
with the enemy again...

76
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,620
It won't take much time
for their soldiers

77
00:05:42,653 --> 00:05:45,286
to fully regroup
and seize the building.

78
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:46,786
Then we should hurry.

79
00:05:55,620 --> 00:05:57,020
[IZUMI]
We get down far enough...

80
00:05:57,053 --> 00:05:59,886
I can easily dig us
an escape tunnel to the streets.

81
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,753
Escape, huh?

82
00:06:01,786 --> 00:06:03,353
That's right...

83
00:06:03,386 --> 00:06:04,620
I don't mean to sound rude,

84
00:06:04,653 --> 00:06:07,753
but you look like you could use
a little breather at this point.

85
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:28,986
We're getting close.

86
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:31,520
So you can
feel it too, huh?

87
00:06:31,553 --> 00:06:34,020
You mean you can sense
his presence or something?

88
00:06:34,053 --> 00:06:36,886
Let's just say I've
got a bad feeling.

89
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,620
The best way
I can explain it is

90
00:06:38,653 --> 00:06:40,886
that my old wounds
are starting to ache.

91
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:43,653
[LOUD THUD]

92
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:48,520
[ED BREATHES DEEPLY]

93
00:06:58,641 --> 00:06:59,641
[ED GASPS]

94
00:07:04,975 --> 00:07:08,391
[GOLD-TOOTH]
Well, now, I wasn't exactly
expecting to have an audience.

95
00:07:08,391 --> 00:07:10,891
You're gonna give
me performance anxiety.

96
00:07:10,924 --> 00:07:12,891
[GOLD-TOOTH LAUGHS]

97
00:07:15,958 --> 00:07:17,391
Who the
hell are you?

98
00:07:17,424 --> 00:07:19,658
How should I answer that?

99
00:07:19,691 --> 00:07:21,524
Hmm...?

100
00:07:21,558 --> 00:07:22,358
You might know me as

101
00:07:22,391 --> 00:07:24,524
the man who
created King Bradley.

102
00:07:24,558 --> 00:07:26,024
[EVERYONE GASPS]

103
00:07:26,058 --> 00:07:29,058
That is my most
proud accomplishment.

104
00:07:29,091 --> 00:07:30,991
You created the Fuhrer?

105
00:07:34,558 --> 00:07:35,891
So it's safe to say...

106
00:07:35,924 --> 00:07:38,724
You're obviously
working with them.

107
00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:40,924
[GOLD-TOOTH]
I didn't realize
that was you...

108
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:43,458
And here I thought you
were at the radio station

109
00:07:43,491 --> 00:07:46,524
when in fact you've come
here to meet me in person...

110
00:07:46,558 --> 00:07:47,958
I can't tell you
how much trouble

111
00:07:47,991 --> 00:07:51,024
you've saved me,
Colonel Mustang.

112
00:07:53,824 --> 00:07:55,791
Why don't you boys keep
them out of my hair

113
00:07:55,824 --> 00:07:57,658
for just a few minutes?

114
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:01,324
[ED GRUNTS]

115
00:08:01,358 --> 00:08:02,458
Who are these guys?

116
00:08:02,491 --> 00:08:04,058
[ROY]
More dummy soldiers?

117
00:08:04,091 --> 00:08:06,691
No... They move
too deliberately...

118
00:08:06,724 --> 00:08:08,591
It's not just on instinct.

119
00:08:08,624 --> 00:08:10,058
[GOLD-TOOTH]
These men were at one time

120
00:08:10,091 --> 00:08:12,824
the other candidates
to become King Bradley.

121
00:08:12,858 --> 00:08:13,858
[ROY AND HAWKEYE GASP]

122
00:08:15,358 --> 00:08:17,558
[ROY]
The men who were
gathered at birth...

123
00:08:17,591 --> 00:08:19,558
Raised by the state...

124
00:08:19,591 --> 00:08:21,424
Specifically educated...

125
00:08:21,458 --> 00:08:22,691
and trained in combat

126
00:08:22,724 --> 00:08:25,658
for the sole purpose
of becoming the Fuhrer.

127
00:08:25,691 --> 00:08:27,691
It took eleven
unsuccessful attempts

128
00:08:27,724 --> 00:08:30,858
before the creation
of King Bradley.

129
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:34,791
So that means... These men...

130
00:08:34,824 --> 00:08:37,791
[GOLD-TOOTH]
You could call them
the leftovers, I guess...

131
00:08:37,824 --> 00:08:39,391
But one thing's certain...

132
00:08:39,424 --> 00:08:40,358
After years of training,

133
00:08:40,391 --> 00:08:42,958
they're skilled warriors
in their own right.

134
00:08:42,991 --> 00:08:47,024
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

135
00:08:47,058 --> 00:08:50,924
They may not be as
powerful as Bradley himself...

136
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:52,958
...but they are strong.

137
00:08:54,558 --> 00:08:56,491
[GUNFIRE]

138
00:08:56,524 --> 00:09:01,524
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

139
00:09:04,491 --> 00:09:09,491
[GUNFIRE]

140
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:18,058
[SEARGENT BREATHES HEAVILY]

141
00:09:18,091 --> 00:09:19,058
Damn...

142
00:09:19,091 --> 00:09:21,291
Miserable traitors.

143
00:09:22,424 --> 00:09:23,258
[BUCCANEER GRUNTS]

144
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:26,391
What a stupid time
to go passing out.

145
00:09:28,591 --> 00:09:29,858
Keep resting!

146
00:09:29,891 --> 00:09:31,658
Forgot about this.

147
00:09:31,691 --> 00:09:32,724
[BUCCANEER GRUNTS]

148
00:09:32,758 --> 00:09:35,858
I better keep it in
or I'll just bleed to death.

149
00:09:35,891 --> 00:09:41,291
[METAL CLANGS]

150
00:09:41,324 --> 00:09:43,324
So he's still goin' strong.

151
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:45,958
[GREED YELLS]

152
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,524
[GREED] Oww!

153
00:09:52,558 --> 00:09:54,058
What the hell, old man?!

154
00:09:54,091 --> 00:09:56,958
It's not like
I meant-- incoming!

155
00:09:58,624 --> 00:10:01,924
[GREED GRUNTS]

156
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:03,524
[GREED]
Cheap son of a bitch.

157
00:10:03,558 --> 00:10:05,924
[METAL CLANGS]

158
00:10:05,958 --> 00:10:07,258
[FU GRUNTS]

159
00:10:13,058 --> 00:10:14,724
[METAL CLANGS]

160
00:10:14,758 --> 00:10:16,491
Certainly makes a
difference when you have

161
00:10:16,524 --> 00:10:18,891
a weapon you're more
comfortable with.

162
00:10:18,924 --> 00:10:19,958
[FU GASPS]

163
00:10:22,958 --> 00:10:24,891
[FU GRUNTS]

164
00:10:24,924 --> 00:10:26,791
[FU GASPS]

165
00:10:26,824 --> 00:10:29,391
[BRADLEY]
It's impressive how
quickly you move...

166
00:10:29,424 --> 00:10:31,391
You're even older than I am.

167
00:10:31,424 --> 00:10:32,291
However...

168
00:10:32,324 --> 00:10:35,391
This is as old as
you're going to get.

169
00:10:40,358 --> 00:10:42,291
Old man Fu! Ahh...!

170
00:10:51,591 --> 00:10:54,358
Well if it isn't
the young prince.

171
00:10:54,391 --> 00:10:55,524
[GREED]
Damn it, Ling!

172
00:10:55,558 --> 00:10:58,058
Ask me before you take over!

173
00:10:58,091 --> 00:10:59,991
I can't help but
recall the last time

174
00:11:00,024 --> 00:11:02,391
we fought when
I took that girl's arm...

175
00:11:02,424 --> 00:11:05,391
It seems that once again
you'd rather risk your own life

176
00:11:05,424 --> 00:11:06,491
than give up
on something

177
00:11:06,524 --> 00:11:08,558
that's not even
worth fighting for.

178
00:11:08,591 --> 00:11:11,358
Young Lord...
Forget me...

179
00:11:11,391 --> 00:11:13,291
My life isn't
worth fighting for.

180
00:11:13,324 --> 00:11:14,491
Don't give me that crap!

181
00:11:14,524 --> 00:11:18,058
Are you honestly telling me
that I should be like him?!

182
00:11:18,091 --> 00:11:20,058
A king should fight
for his people...

183
00:11:20,091 --> 00:11:22,724
...because he is
nothing without them.

184
00:11:22,758 --> 00:11:26,824
This man is about to
sacrifice his own nation.

185
00:11:26,858 --> 00:11:31,758
His people... I'll never
become the monster that he is!

186
00:11:31,791 --> 00:11:35,891
If you truly are a man
worthy to be a king,

187
00:11:35,924 --> 00:11:39,591
you must be able
to accept some loss--

188
00:11:39,624 --> 00:11:41,591
You need to rest! Please!

189
00:11:42,624 --> 00:11:43,991
[FU GRUNTS]

190
00:11:52,391 --> 00:11:53,724
[FU LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

191
00:11:53,758 --> 00:11:56,658
You're right,
Young Lord... I need rest.

192
00:11:56,691 --> 00:11:59,658
Time for this
old man to find rest.

193
00:11:59,691 --> 00:12:01,524
[LING AND GREED YELL]

194
00:12:01,558 --> 00:12:02,824
Harden your shield, Greed!

195
00:12:02,858 --> 00:12:04,791
Protect the Young Lord's body!

196
00:12:04,824 --> 00:12:07,058
[LING GRUNTS]

197
00:12:07,091 --> 00:12:08,524
[LING GASPS]

198
00:12:08,558 --> 00:12:09,924
[FU THINKING]
Young Lord...

199
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:12,891
Become the king
you're meant to be.

200
00:12:14,558 --> 00:12:16,291
But this old servant...

201
00:12:16,324 --> 00:12:19,658
...has no choice but
to offer his retirement!

202
00:12:19,691 --> 00:12:21,424
[EVERYONE GASPS]

203
00:12:22,524 --> 00:12:24,691
[LING AND GREED]
You stubborn fool!

204
00:12:25,958 --> 00:12:29,391
I'm taking you straight
to hell with me, Bradley!

205
00:12:29,424 --> 00:12:31,358
You bastard!

206
00:12:31,391 --> 00:12:32,891
[SLASH]

207
00:12:36,691 --> 00:12:38,291
[FU GRUNTS]

208
00:12:45,558 --> 00:12:48,058
[FU THINKING]
Even while sacrificing myself...

209
00:12:48,091 --> 00:12:51,758
...I still couldn't lay
a single scratch on him.

210
00:12:54,324 --> 00:12:58,658
Young Lord... Please forgive...

211
00:12:58,691 --> 00:13:00,958
...my shameful death.

212
00:13:00,991 --> 00:13:02,424
[BRADLEY GRUNTS]

213
00:13:03,591 --> 00:13:05,391
[BUCCANEER]
That Philosopher's Stone
might have given you

214
00:13:05,424 --> 00:13:07,458
the eyes of a god...

215
00:13:07,491 --> 00:13:09,991
But even you can't
dodge an attack...

216
00:13:10,024 --> 00:13:12,591
...if you can't
see it coming!

217
00:13:12,624 --> 00:13:14,924
[BRADLEY GRUNTS]

218
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:16,458
Alright, old man...

219
00:13:16,491 --> 00:13:18,624
Maybe you are
going to hell...

220
00:13:18,658 --> 00:13:20,724
...but you
aren't goin' alone.

221
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:23,891
I'll keep you company
on the ride down.

222
00:13:23,924 --> 00:13:26,991
Ohhh... You have
my gratitude...

223
00:13:27,024 --> 00:13:29,624
Thank... you.

224
00:13:31,824 --> 00:13:33,424
[BRADLEY GRUNTS]

225
00:13:33,458 --> 00:13:34,558
[BRADLEY YELLS]

226
00:13:36,691 --> 00:13:37,858
Hmm...?

227
00:13:37,891 --> 00:13:40,424
[LING SCREAMS]

228
00:13:48,824 --> 00:13:51,024
[THUD]

229
00:13:54,824 --> 00:13:55,891
[LAN FAN GASPS]

230
00:13:55,924 --> 00:13:58,291
[LAN FAN]
Grandfather!

231
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,577
[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.

232
00:14:06,610 --> 00:14:12,377
[HISSING]

233
00:14:12,410 --> 00:14:15,810
[HEINKEL]
Jeez... First a ditch and
then you run into a lamppost...

234
00:14:15,843 --> 00:14:18,343
Have you ever even
driven a car before?

235
00:14:18,377 --> 00:14:19,343
[YOKI]
Will you shut up?!

236
00:14:19,377 --> 00:14:21,810
It's not my fault that
worthless piece of junk

237
00:14:21,843 --> 00:14:23,543
was impossible to control!

238
00:14:23,577 --> 00:14:24,543
[AL] Calm down,

239
00:14:24,577 --> 00:14:26,610
this is no time
for us to fight!

240
00:14:26,643 --> 00:14:27,643
We've just gotta hurry up

241
00:14:27,677 --> 00:14:30,010
and find a way to
get underground.

242
00:14:32,077 --> 00:14:33,510
Is that...?

243
00:14:36,977 --> 00:14:39,677
That must be from
Colonel Mustang's men.

244
00:14:39,710 --> 00:14:42,843
Let's just hope
that everyone's okay.

245
00:14:42,877 --> 00:14:44,010
Brother.

246
00:14:46,043 --> 00:14:47,710
Let's move!

247
00:14:53,743 --> 00:14:56,077
[METAL CLANGS]

248
00:14:56,110 --> 00:14:59,543
I get it...
These guys are all superhuman.

249
00:14:59,577 --> 00:15:04,843
But... Come on!
This is just ridiculous!

250
00:15:06,410 --> 00:15:08,477
[SCAR GROWLS]

251
00:15:08,977 --> 00:15:13,977
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

252
00:15:21,343 --> 00:15:25,343
[GUNFIRE]

253
00:15:33,410 --> 00:15:34,410
[GUNFIRE]

254
00:15:34,443 --> 00:15:35,377
[ROY GASPS]

255
00:15:37,777 --> 00:15:39,877
You keep leaving your
back wide open, sir.

256
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:41,810
Well I've gotta give
you something to do.

257
00:15:41,843 --> 00:15:42,943
[ROY YELLS]

258
00:15:47,610 --> 00:15:49,810
[IZUMI]
The portal of truth...

259
00:15:49,843 --> 00:15:51,377
I'm sure you're
all familiar with

260
00:15:51,410 --> 00:15:52,910
the alchemist's ultimate sin...

261
00:15:52,943 --> 00:15:55,377
Human transmutation,
of course...

262
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:58,677
If they commit this taboo,
they open the portal...

263
00:15:58,710 --> 00:16:00,977
And they pay the
equivalent price for it.

264
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:03,077
[OLIVIER]
The equivalent price...

265
00:16:03,110 --> 00:16:05,543
Hmm... I take it
you're referring to how

266
00:16:05,577 --> 00:16:07,577
the Elric Brothers
lost their bodies...

267
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:10,577
Tell me, what price
was it that you paid?

268
00:16:13,643 --> 00:16:16,543
I lost part
of my insides.

269
00:16:16,577 --> 00:16:19,610
And then after sacrificing
a part of myself...

270
00:16:19,643 --> 00:16:21,543
I learned the truth.

271
00:16:21,577 --> 00:16:23,743
Human transmutation...

272
00:16:23,777 --> 00:16:26,043
It can't even be performed.

273
00:16:30,122 --> 00:16:33,139
God, I'm sorry...
You must find this dull...

274
00:16:33,139 --> 00:16:35,573
Being a soldier and all.

275
00:16:35,606 --> 00:16:37,473
[ARMSTRONG]
Quite the contrary.

276
00:16:37,506 --> 00:16:40,006
The Homunculi refer to
those unfortunate enough

277
00:16:40,039 --> 00:16:43,639
to have opened the portal
of truth as sacrifices.

278
00:16:43,673 --> 00:16:45,873
That could very likely
be a clue as to what

279
00:16:45,906 --> 00:16:47,906
the enemy has in store.

280
00:16:47,939 --> 00:16:51,806
[OLIVIER]
So then... I take it there
was somebody that you lost...

281
00:16:51,839 --> 00:16:53,973
and you wanted to see
them again so badly...

282
00:16:54,006 --> 00:16:57,806
that you risked opening the
portal and losing your own body?

283
00:17:00,806 --> 00:17:02,673
And what about you?

284
00:17:02,706 --> 00:17:05,439
Don't you have someone
that you'd risk anything

285
00:17:05,473 --> 00:17:07,173
to see one last time?

286
00:17:07,206 --> 00:17:08,439
[OLIVIER LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

287
00:17:08,473 --> 00:17:11,539
That's not really the kind of
thing we soldiers think about.

288
00:17:11,573 --> 00:17:14,906
We don't see any point in
clinging to those who've died.

289
00:17:14,939 --> 00:17:18,006
We only know how to fight
to keep more from dying.

290
00:17:18,039 --> 00:17:20,539
I suppose that
makes sense.

291
00:17:20,573 --> 00:17:23,739
However, I do have
some experience

292
00:17:23,773 --> 00:17:26,939
with what
you've described.

293
00:17:26,973 --> 00:17:29,106
My first encounter
with Edward Elric...

294
00:17:29,139 --> 00:17:31,439
When a Homunculus
invaded Fort Briggs,

295
00:17:31,473 --> 00:17:32,773
Edward blatantly
refused my orders

296
00:17:32,806 --> 00:17:34,439
to tell me what
he knew about it.

297
00:17:34,473 --> 00:17:36,473
At the time, I had not
yet been made aware

298
00:17:36,506 --> 00:17:37,806
that the enemy
had been holding

299
00:17:37,839 --> 00:17:40,173
the life of his
childhood friend hostage.

300
00:17:40,206 --> 00:17:43,039
He just kept repeating:

301
00:17:43,073 --> 00:17:45,573
"I can't answer that."

302
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:46,573
It was quite clear

303
00:17:46,606 --> 00:17:49,039
that any further threat
from me would be wasted.

304
00:17:49,073 --> 00:17:51,639
In that moment, he was
acting neither as a soldier,

305
00:17:51,673 --> 00:17:56,439
nor as a "Dog of
the Military" State Alchemist.

306
00:17:56,473 --> 00:17:57,673
The look in his eyes...

307
00:17:57,706 --> 00:17:59,139
...was desperate.

308
00:17:59,173 --> 00:18:01,073
A boy, willing
to pay any price

309
00:18:01,106 --> 00:18:03,739
to protect the
things he loved.

310
00:18:03,773 --> 00:18:06,906
Hmm... Ed always did have
a knack for being stubborn.

311
00:18:06,939 --> 00:18:09,406
[OLIVIER LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

312
00:18:09,439 --> 00:18:11,073
I'd be lying if I
were to tell you

313
00:18:11,106 --> 00:18:14,173
that I wasn't moved when
I looked into his eyes.

314
00:18:14,206 --> 00:18:15,373
But still...

315
00:18:15,406 --> 00:18:18,739
That doesn't change the fact
that he is a naiÃ¯ve child.

316
00:18:18,773 --> 00:18:21,439
I only hope that he can
help lead us out of this fight

317
00:18:21,473 --> 00:18:24,039
without his naivety burying us.

318
00:18:26,073 --> 00:18:28,173
[GOLD-TOOTH]
That should do fine...

319
00:18:28,206 --> 00:18:31,506
I suppose it's about
time we got started.

320
00:18:31,539 --> 00:18:32,839
[HAWKEYE GRUNTS]

321
00:18:32,873 --> 00:18:34,873
[GUNFIRE]

322
00:18:36,473 --> 00:18:39,173
Now Number Sixteen...
Number Seventeen...

323
00:18:39,206 --> 00:18:40,773
Number Twenty-one...

324
00:18:40,806 --> 00:18:44,173
Number Twenty-Three...
And Number Twenty Six.

325
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:46,539
Come join me.

326
00:18:49,473 --> 00:18:50,673
What's he doing?

327
00:18:53,073 --> 00:18:54,106
[ED GASPS]

328
00:18:54,139 --> 00:18:57,906
Now then! Here goes!

329
00:19:10,206 --> 00:19:11,439
[ED]
What have you done?!

330
00:19:11,473 --> 00:19:14,773
[GOLD-TOOTH]
This...? This right here
is just the beginning.

331
00:19:14,806 --> 00:19:16,573
You seem like a smart boy.

332
00:19:16,606 --> 00:19:18,739
Do you know how
many military operated

333
00:19:18,773 --> 00:19:22,839
alchemy laboratories
there are here in Central?

334
00:19:22,873 --> 00:19:26,906
The last I heard, they've only
got four labs left in the city.

335
00:19:26,939 --> 00:19:28,039
No...

336
00:19:31,106 --> 00:19:35,539
The 5th Laboratory...
They've got five!

337
00:19:35,573 --> 00:19:37,506
It's a transmutation circle...!

338
00:19:37,539 --> 00:19:39,773
The entire city!

339
00:19:39,806 --> 00:19:40,873
You mean...

340
00:19:40,906 --> 00:19:43,806
It's connecting all of the
laboratories into a circle?

341
00:19:53,873 --> 00:19:59,706
[LOUD RUMBLING]

342
00:20:00,906 --> 00:20:01,906
What's happening?!

343
00:20:01,939 --> 00:20:02,739
[HEINKEL GASPS]

344
00:20:05,973 --> 00:20:08,539
[AL]
What's wrong?
Are you okay?

345
00:20:12,539 --> 00:20:14,039
[DOGS BARK]

346
00:20:14,073 --> 00:20:16,806
[HORSES WHINNY]

347
00:20:29,539 --> 00:20:30,706
Izumi.

348
00:20:30,739 --> 00:20:32,006
Yeah...

349
00:20:32,039 --> 00:20:34,906
That's our cue to get
the hell out of here.

350
00:20:36,939 --> 00:20:39,639
We're far enough down
to dig an escape tunnel...

351
00:20:39,673 --> 00:20:41,506
Stand back
a few steps.

352
00:20:41,539 --> 00:20:43,106
[OLIVIER]
Then it's time to part ways.

353
00:20:43,139 --> 00:20:45,173
Huh...?

354
00:20:45,206 --> 00:20:46,539
We're staying.

355
00:20:46,573 --> 00:20:49,639
We can't turn our
backs on this fight now.

356
00:20:49,673 --> 00:20:52,573
We're on a path leading directly
to the heart of the enemy.

357
00:20:52,606 --> 00:20:54,506
We didn't come all
this way just to pass up

358
00:20:54,539 --> 00:20:57,773
the chance to storm in there
and pop some ventricles.

359
00:20:57,806 --> 00:20:59,873
Are you sure
about this?

360
00:21:06,106 --> 00:21:08,373
You saved our lives.

361
00:21:09,506 --> 00:21:11,873
Thanks for your help...
Izumi Curtis.

362
00:21:11,906 --> 00:21:14,839
Don't mention it...
Good luck, General Armstrong.

363
00:21:28,939 --> 00:21:34,739
[GOLD-TOOTH LAUGHS]

364
00:21:37,206 --> 00:21:38,506
[ED GRUNTS]

365
00:21:38,539 --> 00:21:39,906
[ED GASPS]

366
00:21:45,073 --> 00:21:46,439
[ED, IZUMI, AND AL]
What?!

367
00:21:46,473 --> 00:21:49,039
[IZUMI SCREAMS]

368
00:21:49,073 --> 00:21:53,006
[AL SCREAMS]

369
00:21:53,039 --> 00:21:56,506
[ED SCREAMS]

370
00:21:56,539 --> 00:21:58,806
[AL SCREAMS]

371
00:22:00,539 --> 00:22:01,806
[MARCOH]
Alphonse!

372
00:22:01,839 --> 00:22:03,706
[IZUMI SCREAMS]

373
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:04,939
Izumi!

374
00:22:06,906 --> 00:22:08,906
Izumi, no!

375
00:22:09,673 --> 00:22:13,373
[ED SCREAMS]

376
00:22:17,206 --> 00:22:19,539
No...! Fullmetal!

377
00:22:21,473 --> 00:22:28,673
[ED SCREAMS]

378
00:22:28,706 --> 00:22:32,739
You... bastard!

379
00:24:04,039 --> 00:24:08,006
[NARRATOR]
Anger is born from the
extreme depths of human sorrow.

380
00:24:08,039 --> 00:24:09,173
And when two souls,

381
00:24:09,206 --> 00:24:12,639
both shaken to their very
core with the rage of loss,

382
00:24:12,673 --> 00:24:15,039
attempt to control
the same body,

383
00:24:15,073 --> 00:24:18,406
they will only unleash
true annihilation.

384
00:24:18,439 --> 00:24:21,773
Next time on Fullmetal
Alchemist: Brotherhood.

385
00:24:21,806 --> 00:24:25,139
Episode 58: Sacrifices.

386
00:24:26,839 --> 00:24:28,673
His only desire

387
00:24:28,706 --> 00:24:33,006
was to continue protecting
him... even after his demise.

